text: Maloyuldybayevo () is a rural locality (a village) in Yuldybayevsky Selsoviet, Zilairsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 208 as of 2010. There are 3 streets. == Geography == It is located 43 km from Zilair, 3 km from Yuldybayevo. == References == Category:Rural localities in Zilairsky District
title: Maloyuldybayevo
